Feature: Create Contact Notes API - Invalid Subject Values

  Scenario Outline: Verify the Post Contact Notes API with empty or overly long subject
    Given Send Request to get Authentication Token for ICOS
    When I generate the JWT Token
    And Send request to generate New Person with below details
      | firstName       | <firstName>    |
      | lastName        | Lastname       |
      | subType         | pers_form_ass  |
      | domicileCountry | CH             |
      | gender          | male           |
      | nationality     | CH             |
    Then Send POST ContactNote Request with below details
      | subject      | <subject>     |
      | notes        | <notes>       |
      | hasFollowup  | <hasFollowup> |
    And I verify the Status Code for Contact Notes "<statusCode>"
    And I verify the <errorType> with below details
      | description   | <description> |
      | error message | <error>       |

  Examples:
    | firstName   | subject            | notes    | hasFollowup | statusCode | errorType        | description        | error                                            |
    | FirstName_1 | EMPTY_SUBJECT      | Testnote | false       | 500        | error response   |                    | Mandatory field: Subject\nPlease enter a subject |
    | FirstName_1 | RANDOM_GREATER_250 | Testnote | false       | 400        | validation error | Validation Errors  | subject too long (max 250)                       |
